27/11/2007
TIRANA, Albania -- Police on Monday (November 26th) seized a record two tonnes of cannabis allegedly hidden inside a truck at the Greek-Albanian border. The driver, Isuf Duka, 50, was arrested. The stash has an estimated street value of 2m euros.
In other news Monday, thousands of Albanian women protested against domestic violence, demanding that the police better respond to such cases. Sunday marked an international day calling for an end to violence against women. According to a recent Amnesty International report, one out of four Albanian women living in urban areas is a victim, with a higher rate suspected in rural areas. (AP, RBK, Makfax, Blic, Javno.com, A1, Balkanweb - 26/11/07)
